Notation of an Algorithm

An algorithm is a finite sequence of well defined instructions
to solve a problem or perform a computation.

Properties:
Finiteness
Definiteness
Input
Output
Effectiveness

#include<iostream>
using namespace std;
int main(){
    int n,sum=0;
    cin>>n;
    for(int i=1;i<=n;i++)
    sum+=i;
    cout<<"Sum"<<sum;
}

